values:
Ayan, still alive and surviving as always, still working on my latest fanfic, but it's in Filipino... uh, can I rant in my native tongue for a moment? Ehem...

Anak ng patola, gising pa ako sa mga oras na ito. Kung sa palagay n'yo nasa kalagitnaan ako ngayon ng trabaho, nagkakakamali kayo. Sa ngayon hindi ako makapag-work dahil sa istupidong PC ko na nagkaaberya na naman ang power supply at tila MIA ang aming technician, di siya ma-contact kahit ng boss namin, at nakailang text at email na ako, sumagot nga, tinanong lang kung anong nangyari sa PC ko, Sinabi ko ang problema, tapos di na ulit nag-reply. The end. Saklap, noh? Lapit na ng kinsenas, wala pa rin akong nagagawa. Muzhta naman!?

Too bad, wala pa along balak na mag-resign, kelangan ko munang paabutin ng isang taon ang stay ko sa una kong trabaho para naman me mailagay naman ako sa aking resume 'pag naghanap na ulit ako ng bago. Konting tiis pa. August na, sunod na buwan, papasok na ang -ber month, yahoo.

Sa ngayon, nakikigamit lang ako ng laptop ng kapatid ko para lang mag-type. Hindi ito puwedeng gamitin sa work ko, dahil bukod sa dadalhin niya ito sa barko, magkakaproblema 'pag naglagay ako ng sarili kong program dito. Pero nag-promise naman siya na bibilhan niya ako ng laptop kapalit ng binili kong Angry Birds (TM) shirt niya, wahahaha! Basta ba hati kami sa bayad, walang problema. WAHOO! Magkaka-laptop na akoooh!!!! :D

Oh well, eto ang hirap 'pag sanay ka na sa puyatan, di ka na makatulog tulad ng dati. Pero konting tiis, malay mo everything will be okay. Sure ako diyan :D

End of rant...

Okay, before I forgot, I have to thank whoever uploaded Tenipuri 100 Song Marathon, Tenipuri Festa 2009 and 2011 on YouTube! You're a GOD! Arigatou gozaimasu!!! Although yeah, we all know that YouTube has this habit of removing videos--of hell, check this link while lasts!

www.youtube.com/user/ThaoHo987

Check the vids people, it's worth a treat to all PoT Fans! WOOHOO! :D

HI! just to tell you all that I'M STILL ALIVE.... and busy. Sorry if I haven't updated my journal for a long, long time. AAAAGH! Yeah, I'm working now. WORKING. Finally got a job since December kaya busy na ang lola moh. Anyway, just to tell you that I decided to create another account, this time, dedicated to KATEKYO HITMAN REBORN.

He-he, dunno, but I got hooked two years ago because of the plot. Naloka akoh! So I've been watching this till the 'end' and still reading the latest manga chapter. Malayo na ang narating nito't it's not yet over! For this, my creative juices start to flow again and must be freed while I still can.

Itong bagong account na ito ay para sa lahat ng fanfics ko sa KHR IN FILIPINO. Yep, No English works, sorry people. Pero if you're looking for the translated fics, you can visit my FanFiction account: www.fanfiction.net/~beafstakes  at nandoon ang iba ko pang fics with English translation. And well... para na rin makahingi ng tulong sa kapwa ko Filipino na i-translate ang mga gawa ko. Hindi, hindi sa tinatamad ako (although inaamin ko madali akong tamarin) o sa hindi ako marunong mag-translate. Sobrang busy ko wala na akong halos time. Buti nga magkaka-oras pa ako sa pagsusulat 'pag walang pasok, eh...

So yeah. I'll be making a new account for Reborn. Abangan n'yo na lang people! Sorry po sa mga naabala ko ^_^

Halloween has passed, All Saints' Day has passed, All Souls' Day has passed, and yet I still added NOTHING in here. But as I promised, yes, the POT Illustrated Fanfiction project will go on as planned, I just need time and of course, money. I STILL DON'T HAVE A GODDAMN JOB! Grrr... I tried to apply for CSR somewhere in Alabang but it was an epic failure. What the hell is happening in this forsaken country!?
But still I keep on hoping that someday I could handle my own finances before let's say Christmas. I'm really desperate right now. So desperate that once again I'm so lazy keeping up my FanFiction acount. May God help me with this... :(

I'm trying to be visible to all so I updated my FanFiction account. Princess Idol's already in Stanza 3, both in Filipino and English. For those who want to read it, here's the link:

www.fanfiction.net/s/5093207/1/Princess_Idol_THE_ENGLISH_VERSION

www.fanfiction.net/s/5093203/1/Princess_Idol

Illustrations for my upcoming fanfic is still unfinished so please bear with me... ^_^ And thanks nga pala for those who had read and reviewed my works! :D For comments and suggestions, feel free to comment on my FanFiction Acocunt or here. Ja! ^_^

Well, whaddyuknow, I'm ALIVE, alive, and still looking for a goddamn job. He-he, sorry for the early swearing. Anywayz, it's been a LONG long time since I updated my account, because first of all, I'm so damn busy hunting for a job, second, I'm a bit tired of updating my account, and third, I almost forgot my password. That's one major problem when it comes to online blogging, especially if your password's too long to memorize that you can't access to your own account till you'll end up tired and giving up. But for the sake of my poor fanfics that can only be read in my trusty handy dandy notebook, I decided to revive my account and this time, I'll try my best to put up illustrated works of mine regarding the featured fanfic.

Although I have my FanFiction account, I also have a hard time updating it. I'm already in the third chapter of my latest PoT fanfic Princess Idol but I have to translate it in English for the sake of foreign readers because not all FanFiction users are Filipino and the Philippines is not just the only country in Asia and in this world. The worst part was that I got sick while updating my work so it ended up in a short hiatus, or maybe longer, it will depend if I could still keep it up. Well, some of my fics there, mostly non-PoT, ended up hanging in nowhere. I even discontinued one of them.

And YES, I decided to keep going on, as Sanada's song would say. My creative juices get easily activated once I see something interesting to put in my PoT fanfiction, so instead of putting it into waste, I thought of putting those here. Yep, here. So that illustrations could be included, too, you know what I mean. Sometimes FanFiction.net can be boring since they don't support pictures for the stories. Well I'm a vision-oriented person, I can't stand reading a story without even a single picture. And it gave me an idea when I visited my DeviantArt account today (of course I draw! Yeahbaby!) and saw two PoT fanarts there involving Ryuzaki Sakuno, entitled Hysteric Moon. I knew right away it was a fanfiction and the author sketched the concept of the story to advertise it and to make it more interesting to the readers, so I'll give her a credit for that.

For this, without further ado, the Prince of Tennis Illustrated Fanfiction Project is officially OPEN. (Wooh! Palakpakan naman jan, people!)

For starters, I present to you my second PoT fanfiction (the first one's on my FanFiction Account), entitled Prism Siren. It is an AU (alternative universe) fic, an adventure-fantasy-supernatural-romance story set a year after the Nationals, that means our beloved seniors here have already graduated. This will mostly set in Seigaku so that means it will be Kaidoh and Momo's life during their last year in middle school. And it will be Kaidoh-centric, or should I say, will give more focus to our little mamushi and his unknown bestfriend, a female, YES he has a bestfriend here and it's a girl, and their complicated relationship especially if witchcraft and crystals are involved. And everybody knows that Kaidoh is scared of anything paranormal. How he would handle that will depend on the outcome of the story. Yes, there will be numerous OCs and a lot of OOCness and surprises that will surely make yourselves scratch your heads in confusion, but your eyes will pop also, he-he. You'll find out sooner or later. The whol fic will be in English for the convenience of our foreign surfers, but I'll also do it in Filipino for our fellow kababayans.

Ah, the main summary and the main characters of this story will be on the separate entry. Plase wait for that. Better yet, please bear with meeeh....

The truth is that I've done several drawings for this story and I still can't scan it yet and show it to people because of my first fic. So I guess this is a good solution so that my frustrations will be over.

If you're wondering how I did Princess Idol and why I keep mantioning it here, just visit my FanFiction account:  http://www.fanfiction.net/~beafstakes

Or if you want to visit my DeviantArt account and be convinced that I draw, here it is: http://bipura.deviantart.com/ It's slightly updated, though. Well what do you expect for someone who doesn't have a scanner and has to pay several bucks and save the humiliation (sus, wag ka naah!) just to scan my precious works? Oh, I forgot to thank hakase-sempai for scanning most of my works there for free. I owe him bigtime.

Well, that's it. just wait for my update (if you can keep waiting, hu-hu...). Please pray for me so that my laziness won't screw me. I have to do this for the sake of fandom! WOOH! Support me, minna! MWAH-MWAH-MWAH! :)

Uh...it's been... dunno, a YEAR since I used this account. Sorry, minna. Probably grew tired of using LiveJournal for several reasons: first, I just graduated last year. Second, I'm busy looking for a job, and third, we have only ONE computer at home so don't expect me to update everyday. Kahit 'yung iba ko pang blogs, hindi ko na rin masyadong ina-update, ito pa kaya!?

Owkies, for starters, the reason why I opened this up again to seek help. I'll get straight...

WHO AMONG YOU DOES HAVE ANY IDEA WHERE I COULD FIND TORRENTS AND/OR ORDERS FOR TENIPURI 100 SONG MARATHON?

Hu-hu-hu... :'( I really wanted it...promise... I'm trying to find downloads for this but whatta heck, IT'S NOT FREE. But hey, what do you expect? Besides, it's copyrighted, so I really need to have a goddamn job to hae my own money to buy the DVD! Brrrr.... 

Wait--I forgot, our CD drive doesn't work pala... Oh great.

Ok, say what you want, but I'm so damn desperate! Please, please, people of the world, if you heed this message, please reply! Anything will be appreciated, I just need yer answers! Hu-hu...! :'(

I'll end my sentiments here. Thanks in advance and God bless us all! :)

This is my FIRST entry since my Livejournal was put under sudden hiatus.

RAKENROL!!!! Woot-woot! Yeh! After waiting for almost three months I was able to watch snippets of this historical event in TeniPuri History! Poor, poor me, I can't afford to buy the DVD for myself, tch. But thanks to YouTube, I was able to watch even if they are just parts of the whole event.

Anyway, here are my comments to some of the footages of TeniPuri 100 Song Marathon happened last March 16 at the Pacifico Yokohama. Thirty-three seiyuus from this super-popular sports anime were gathered to perform for their fans all over Japan and the rest of the world (I'm sure there are some foreigner fanatics who went there for this, how I wish I was there, too... :( ). This is not yet complete, I still mave to watch ALL the performances, and that's my goal for now: to watch every single performance they made on that concert. Oh, well...

1.) Future (performed by all seiyuus)---that's obvious, since this song became the trademark of the whole series. The moment you hear it, you would say, "Ah, that's from PoT."
 
2.) Freedom and 3.) Don't Look Back (by AOZU)---MineJun's sooo adorable! 

4.) ROCK 54!? and 5.) Tonde! Mawatte! Mata Raishuu! (by Caps n' Bins)---So rockin' full of energy, and I personally LOVE the Nyan-Nyan Dance! (lemme guess: did Takahashi-san planned this?) *doing the Nyan-Nyan Dance*

6.) Dreaming On The Radio (by Minegawa Junko as Echizen Ryoma)---She carried herself well during the performance. As I said, she's sooo adorable (and I like her shoes!)

7.) Niji (by Okiayu Ryoutarou as Tezuka Kunimitsu)---one word: HOT. Why hot? I never thought that Okki-san can be THAT hot in his outfit while doing the song! *faints*

8.) Asobi ni Ikenai Ka? (by Kawamoto Naru as Kawamura Takashi)---one of my personal favorites. It might not sounded as lively as its studio version, but I love it anyway!

9.) DISTANCE (by Tsuda Kenjiro as Inui Sadaharu)---he did a skit of him as Inui while atending to his laptop, then to his dramatic performance. Nice one...! 

10.) SHUTTER CHANCE wa Ichido Dake! ~ pinpoint smash version (by Kaida Yuki as Fuji Syusuke)---She's gorgeous! This was the first time I've heard this song and it was SOOO gorgeous! Gorgeous as her character!

11.) Chain Reaction (by Koyasu Kouhei as Kaidoh Kaoru)---Headbangin' rock and roll performance! Loves the jump part! His outfit suits his song perfectly! RAKENROL!

12.) Hontou no Kimochi (by Kondo Takayuki as Oishi Shuichiro)---So Oishi, as I must say. He's really into character especially in his song.

13.) Come Together (by Takahashi Hiroki as Kikumaru Eiji)---KAWAII! The song and the seiyuu's SOO adorable! He's so different when he played Harima Kenji in the School Rumble Musical! Totally in character!

14.) SAYONARA (by Onosaka Masaya as Momoshiro Takeshi)--also one of my favorites since it brings out the other side of Momo's character. He's so emo when he performed the song... *cries*

23.) Next Gate (by Kosuda Toshiyuki as Shishido Ryo and Namikawa Daisuke as Ohtori Chotarou)---What I like here is when they did their doubled formation (which, sad to say, I forgot what it is called). And who could ever thought that Shishido can actually rap? That was awesome!

24.) Charm Point ha Naki Bokuro (by Suwabe Jun'ichi as Atobe Keigo and the rest of Hyotei)---Can't stop laughing at this one! Suwabe-san in BOA FEATHERS. I love the German countoff and the cheer! Atobeng-Atobe ang lolo moh!

34.) White Line (by AOZU)---one of my all-time faves. The song was made a pitch higher for the performance. The blending is so dreamy... so different from the Studio Version. Love-Love!

35.) Ometto Samba (by Caps n' Bins)---as usual, it's full of energy, laughable (ayos ang term!) and enjoyable. But what are THOSE girls in miniskirts doing at the back!?

36.) DEPARTURES (by AOZU and Caps n' Bins)---another favorite, probably the only song performed by all Seigaku Regulars. Love this version (and Kiyasu was trying to reach that high note! Ganbare!)!

41.) Gontakure (by the seiyuu of Touyama Kintaro---I can't see her name in the list!)---Truly in the character. Although messy, at least she's in the character which most fans enjoyed.

42.) Bible (by Yoshimasa Hosoya as Shiraishi Kuranosuke)---never thought that this song's beautiful! So is the seiyuu's voice, I'll add this to my favorites!

43.) Brilliant Brain (by Osuka Jun as Chitose Senri)---the song's a bit weird to me, weirder that Gontakure. Is the seiyuu drunk? Oh well, that's his character...

46. Ya-Ki-Ni-Ku (by Tong Buta)---can't stop laughing in this song! Especially with the OVA 20 at the background, oh juicekoh! (whoe, Tsuroka Satoshi (the voice of Kabaji) is actually a handsome guy...!)

51. Brand New Days (by Shishido and Ohtori)---another memorable song. So refreshing. Is Kosuda-san a J-pop artist?

56-58.) Valentine Kiss (by Atobe, Kiuchi Hidenobu as Oshitari Yuushi and Kusanoki Taiten as Sanada Genichirou with the rest of Rikkai and Hyotei)---Boa Feathers, swinging butts, shalalala, girls in uniforms, feeling Kokushou Sayuri. But it's an adorable performance! (Taiten screams KISS in the end. Gives me the creeps~!)


93.) Odorimasen Ka? Meganes and 94.) Sayonara Meganes (by of course, The Meganes)---that woman danced in their performence was so lucky that she was able to get close to those three. (Mhen...!). So sexy! But too bad when they performed their final song (and I mean FINAL), I was saddened to hear that that will be their last single. Their meganes were their evidence when they left them on stage... *cries*

95.) Koi no Gekidasa Ecstacy (by Tachikiritai)---I'm sooo in LOVE with their dance number! It rocks, it's grooving me, a totally-beautiful performance!

96.) Fujiori (by Hyotei Eternity)---they came out in their shining silver attire just like in the cover. So Hyotei. They even posed like in the cover! 

97.) Kakaeta Kiseki (by AOZU)---again, so AOZU. MineJun remained adorable, and I like the song (the kira-kira motion they did was good!).

98.) Thank YOU! (by Caps n' Bins)---their first song ever heard in the sereis itself, although it's OVA. Love the tune, it reminds me of Asaka Yui's 'Believe Again', it's an 80's song.

100.) Dear Prince~Tennis no Oujisama-tachi E (by Ikemen Samurai and the rest of the seiyuus PLUS Konomi-sensei himself)---so dramatic, although lively, I can't help but to cry in this performance (music was done by none other than Konomi-sensei. Forgot who wrote the lyrics. This was a memorable song since it was frist seen in the final chapter of PoT Manga.)

102.) We Love TENIPURI (by the seiyuus)---adapted from We Love SEIGAKU. I'm telling you now: THIS SONG SHOULD HAVE A SINGLE! Even just a memorial single as long as it has a SINGLE!   

You would notice that I skipped some numbers since I've never seen some of them. Kaya nga part 1, hindi bah? Mhen, I wish I could really have a DVD of this... I can't comment on the whole event right now, but as soon as I've seen it all, you will read what's on my mind about this. Thanks to YouTube. Whooh!

CREDITS to:
arubaito

MUZHTA NA, MGA PASHNEA???

Ai, kay tagal ding di ako nakabalik. Kakaimbyerna kase ang ating Linggo. Tong Linggong 'to, oo, ngarag ang lola moh! Drama, paper, reports, HASSLE! Kelangan mo pang pagsabayin 'yon sa loob ng isang linggo, muzhta naman??? Ai...

Anyweiz, andito na rin lang ako, nararapat lang na ituloy ko na ito. The gentle vice-captain, who always sacrifices himself to achieve what's best for their team. He always worries about the well-being of others, and never about himself, aside being political-minded, thus earning him the title "Mother of Seigaku".
Oishi has 101% patience, and more than once did he have to put up with Eiji's unreasonable tantrums, but he never got angry. No wonder Eiji relies on him so much. Only such an ever-patient and understanding player such as Oishi would be worthy of becoming Seigaku's vice-captain. Siya ang tipo ng estudyanteng 'mas inaalala pa ang kalagayan at karapatan ng kanyang mga kagrupo't kaklase kesa sa grades niya sa Algebra' (Bob Ong, 2000)

Oishi uses this when he's swimming or when he wants to raise his focus during a match. Pano pag me tumawag sa kanya eh di di niya narinig???

Pills (DRUGS??? STEROIDS????? INAYYYY!!!!!!!!!!!!!)

The happy-go-lucky sunshine boy of Seigaku. Carefree and optimistic, he always looks on the bright side of things, never giving up hope even in the worst of times. His vigor and spirit is often an inspiration to the Seigaku regulars.
Though he is a 3rd year, Eiji is without a doubt the most child-like regular in Seigaku. Reasons for this may be that he is the youngest in 5 children. With 2 older sisters and brothers to spoil him, no wonder he can be so immature and stubborn at times.
And aside from being the isip-bata of the team, he's also a nekojin (catperson) where intentionally or not his face and utterances turns into a cat-like one, and it makes him even looked CUTER! Meowwwww............

INSIDE HIS BAG

Notebook
Eiji carries this around just in case, but according to Inui's observations, the chances of him actually using it is quite low.

Toothpaste & Toothbrush Set
To keep his teeth sparkling white and to be spotted by talent scouts (he-he...), Eiji always carries this around with him.

Snacks
Always hungry after exercising, Eiji will bring snacks with him everytime there is practice. So me tumalo na rin ke Momo...

MP3 Player
Eiji's hobby while commuting to and from school is listening to music, so an mp3 player is definitely a must-have for him. Gosh, wanna have one, too...

Hair Wax (ngek?)
His hairstyle will mess up after excessive exercising (muzhta naman di ba eh puros tambling ang nagagawa niya sa practice?), so Eiji carries his favorite brand of wax with him to fix it up.

Comb
This is used along with the hair wax, and due to Eiji's amazing skills, it only takes around 3 minutes to fix his hair na parang nagpa-salon ke Ricky Reyes.

Band-aid
Eiji's trademark. But why he wears it and why he wanted to be like Nelly is still a mystery...

The regulars will play cards during a practice break (oi, bawal 'yan, ah!), or Eiji will use it to perform a new magic trick he learned (David Blane, iz dat YOU???).

Muli ay kailangan ko muling mamaalam. Pero di pa tapos! Naisip kong tapusin ko na lang ang mga lihim ng mga taong ito bago na tayo dumako sa karugtong ng nabitin kong kuwento. Matutong maghintay, sapagkat pinagpapala ang mga taong matiisin at matiyaga! Magtiyaga upang magka-nilaga! Hanggang sa susunod mga pashnea! AVISALA!

(este ang mga impormasyong ito ay ninakaw lang sa Genius 10.0 ngehe...)

Pinapatay ko ngayon ang oras ko sa dahilang WALANG UMATEND NG AMING PRACTICE KUNDI AKO LANG--MAG-ISA. Muzhta naman? At ako pa ang bida ng drama namin--LYSISTRATA. Muzhta naman ang name? Pero, nackow, imbyerna ako kahit di naman halata.

Magkaganoon pa man nagbalik ako upang hindi na magpaliguy-ligoy pa kung sino ang susunod sa Seigaku lineup. Whether you like it or NOT--andito ang resident DATA SPECIALIST ng team at ang loob ng kanyang bag at pagkatao. Nyaknyaknyaknyaknyaknyaknyak..... :D

HELLO, PEOPLE OF THE PHILIPPINES, MABUHAY!!!!! Welcome po sa aking walang-kuwentang journal. Censya na't ang sama ng pagbati ko... Anyweiz, dito ninyo mababasa't masasaksihan ang galaw ng aking pag-uutak: mga panaginip, pangarap, listahan ng mga utang, wishlist, mga larawang may pampanirang-caption and most of all, mga FANFICS and ORIGINALS, yes, mga likhang-kamay na tanging DITO ninyo lang makikita't wala sa fanfiction.net! Saka ko na lang ipapapaliwanag sa inyo kung bakit...

At ang aking buena-mano: isang PoT fanfic in Filipino! PoT stands for THE PRINCE OF TENNIS, mapapalabas sa QTV Channel 11, sister station ng GMA-7. Muzhta naman ang isa sa mga kauna-unahang anime ng bagong-silang na istasyong ito? Grabe, mhen, first time ko pa lang ito napanood, as in WHOE, ang cool-et! Astig na tennis moves, mga kalalakihang hanggang pangarap mo na lang mahahagkan (ah, ganoon?), mga patweetums na tambalan, at mga kakapangmura't kakalokang eksena. Kala mo nanonood ka ng Bagets starring William Martinez, Aga Mulach, Raymond Lauchengco, Herbert Bautista, and JC Bonin (di ko siya kilala)kase di lang tennis ang main attraction ng kuwento, pagkat napapaloob din dito ang mga kuwentong adolescence, as in--ehem--crush-crush, responsibilidad, pagharap sa mga hamon ng buhay sa pagitan ng pagiging bata at teenager, at mga kuwentong...PUSA. Ngek... Ai naku, kung alam n'yo 'tong sinasabi ko, feel free to comment! He-he...

Anak naman ng pating, kung saan-saan na ako nakakarating ah, wala pa ako sa point ko.  Malas pa, wala na akong oras, hay naku... me test pa naman kami sa Art App ngayon, so sorry, guys, next post na lang ulet. Promise, yung unang post ko yung hinihintay ninyong fanfic ko (hinihintay n'yo bang talaga? Oh well...) Pa'no, mga nilalang, hanggang sa susunod!!!
